# README.md

# OpenAI Function Calling Integration

This project provides a comprehensive implementation of OpenAI's function calling feature, enabling seamless integration between AI models and external tools. The system supports multiple model providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, and Google), offers advanced tool management, and provides extensive customization options.

## Table of Contents

- [Features](#features)
- [Quick Start](#quick-start)
- [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Advanced Features](#advanced-features)
- [Configuration](#configuration)
- [Examples](#examples)
- [API Reference](#api-reference)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
- [License](#license)

## Features

### Core Functionality
- **Multi-Provider Support**: Works with OpenAI, Anthropic, and Google model providers
- **Function Calling**: Automatic tool invocation based on AI model responses
- **Tool Management**: Dynamic tool registration and discovery
- **Streaming Support**: Real-time response streaming with progress callbacks
- **Error Handling**: Comprehensive error handling and retry mechanisms

### Advanced Features
- **Tool Discovery**: Automatic tool discovery using DuckDuckGo search
- **Memory Management**: Context-aware conversation history with token management
- **Custom Tools**: Easy creation and registration of custom tools
- **Batch Processing**: Support for batch tool calls and parallel execution
- **Rate Limiting**: Built-in rate limiting and retry strategies
- **Monitoring**: Extensive logging and performance metrics

### Development Features
- **TypeScript Support**: Full TypeScript definitions and type safety
- **Testing Framework**: Comprehensive test suite with Jest
- **Documentation**: Auto-generated API documentation
- **Hot Reloading**: Development mode with automatic tool reloading

## Installation

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18.0 or higher
- npm or yarn package manager
- API keys for your chosen model providers

### Basic Installation

```bash
npm install @openai/function-calling
# or
yarn add @openai/function-calling
# or
pnpm add @openai/function-calling
```

### Environment Setup

Create a `.env` file in your project root:

```env
# Required: Choose your model provider
PROVIDER=openai  # or 'anthropic' or 'google'

# Required: API Keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_api_key
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key

# Optional: Configuration
MAX_TOKENS=4096
TEMPERATURE=0.7
MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
STREAMING_ENABLED=true
```

## Quick Start

### Basic Usage

```typescript
import { OpenAIFunctionCalling } from '@openai/function-calling';

// Initialize the function calling system
const functionCalling = new OpenAIFunctionCalling({
  provider: 'openai',
  apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY,
  model: 'gpt-4o-mini'
});

// Define a simple tool
const weatherTool = {
  name: 'getWeather',
  description: 'Get weather information for a city',
  parameters: {
    type: 'object',
    properties: {
      city: {
        type: 'string',
        description: 'The city to get weather for'
      }
    },
    required: ['city']
  },
  handler: async ({ city }: { city: string }) => {
    // Your weather API logic here
    return { city, temperature: 72, condition: 'Sunny' };
  }
};

// Register the tool
functionCalling.registerTool(weatherTool);

// Make a function call
const response = await functionCalling.callFunction({
  prompt: 'What is the weather in San Francisco?',
  tools: ['getWeather']
});

console.log(response);
```

### Advanced Usage

```typescript
import { OpenAIFunctionCalling } from '@openai/function-calling';

// Initialize with advanced configuration
const functionCalling = new OpenAIFunctionCalling({
  provider: 'openai',
  apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY,
  model: 'gpt-4o',
  maxTokens: 8000,
  temperature: 0.3,
  streamingEnabled: true,
  rateLimiting: {
    enabled: true,
    maxRetries: 3,
    retryDelay: 1000
  }
});

// Create a custom tool with streaming support
const streamingTool = {
  name: 'processData',
  description: 'Process data with streaming updates',
  parameters: {
    type: 'object',
    properties: {
      data: { type: 'array', items: { type: 'string' } }
    },
    required: ['data']
  },
  handler: async ({ data }: { data: string[] }) => {
    // Process data with streaming updates
    for (let i = 0; i < data.length; i++) {
      await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 100));
      // Send progress update
      functionCalling.sendProgress({
        tool: 'processData',
        progress: (i + 1) / data.length,
        message: `Processing item ${i + 1} of ${data.length}`
      });
    }
    return { processed: data.length, result: 'completed' };
  }
};

// Register tools
functionCalling.registerTool(streamingTool);

// Set up progress callback
functionCalling.onProgress((progress) => {
  console.log(`Progress: ${progress.tool} - ${progress.progress * 100}%`);
});

// Call with streaming
const response = await functionCalling.callFunction({
  prompt: 'Process this data: ["item1", "item2", "item3"]',
  tools: ['processData'],
  streaming: true
});

console.log(response);
```

## Usage

### Configuration Options

```typescript
interface FunctionCallingConfig {
  provider: 'openai' | 'anthropic' | 'google';
  apiKey: string;
  model: string;
  maxTokens?: number;
  temperature?: number;
  streamingEnabled?: boolean;
  rateLimiting?: {
    enabled: boolean;
    maxRetries: number;
    retryDelay: number;
  };
  logging?: {
    level: 'debug' | 'info' | 'warn' | 'error';
    enabled: boolean;
  };
}
```

### Tool Definition

```typescript
interface ToolDefinition {
  name: string;
  description: string;
  parameters: {
    type: 'object';
    properties: Record<string, any>;
    required: string[];
  };
  handler: (args: Record<string, any>) => Promise<any>;
  streaming?: boolean;
  rateLimit?: number;
}
```

### Function Calling Methods

```typescript
// Basic function call
const response = await functionCalling.callFunction({
  prompt: string,
  tools?: string[],
  streaming?: boolean
});

// Batch function calls
const responses = await functionCalling.batchCallFunction([
  { prompt: 'First request', tools: ['tool1'] },
  { prompt: 'Second request', tools: ['tool2'] }
]);

// Tool discovery
const discoveredTools = await functionCalling.discoverTools({
  query: 'Find tools for image processing',
  maxResults: 5
});
```

## Advanced Features

### Custom Tool Creation

```typescript
import { BaseTool } from '@openai/function-calling';

class CustomTool extends BaseTool {
  constructor() {
    super({
      name: 'customTool',
      description: 'A custom tool with advanced features',
      parameters: {
        type: 'object',
        properties: {
          input: { type: 'string' }
        },
        required: ['input']
      }
    });
  }

  async execute(args: { input: string }): Promise<any> {
    // Custom logic here
    return { result: `Processed: ${args.input}` };
  }
}

// Register the custom tool
functionCalling.registerTool(new CustomTool());
```

### Memory Management

```typescript
// Set conversation memory
functionCalling.setMemory({
  maxTokens: 4096,
  history: [],
  context: {}
});

// Get memory usage
const memoryUsage = functionCalling.getMemoryUsage();
console.log(`Memory usage: ${memoryUsage.tokens} tokens`);

// Clear memory
functionCalling.clearMemory();
```

### Error Handling

```typescript
try {
  const response = await functionCalling.callFunction({
    prompt: 'Your request here',
    tools: ['tool1']
  });
} catch (error) {
  if (error.code === 'RATE_LIMITED') {
    console.log('Rate limit exceeded, retrying...');
    // Handle rate limiting
  } else if (error.code === 'TOOL_NOT_FOUND') {
    console.log('Tool not found, checking available tools...');
    // Handle missing tools
  } else {
    console.error('Unexpected error:', error);
  }
}
```

## Examples

### Weather Information Tool

```typescript
import { OpenAIFunctionCalling } from '@openai/function-calling';

const functionCalling = new OpenAIFunctionCalling({
  provider: 'openai',
  apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY,
  model: 'gpt-4o-mini'
});

// Weather tool
const weatherTool = {
  name: 'getWeather',
  description: 'Get current weather information',
  parameters: {
    type: 'object',
    properties: {
      city: { type: 'string', description: 'City name' },
      units: { 
        type: 'string', 
        enum: ['metric', 'imperial'], 
        description: 'Temperature units' 
      }
    },
    required: ['city']
  },
  handler: async ({ city, units = 'metric' }) => {
    // Mock weather API
